%N A391424 Positive discriminants of orders of quadratic fields with form class number 2.
%C A391424 Not to be confused with A344408, the positive discriminants of orders of quadratic fields with class number 2.
%C A391424 Let h(D) and h+(D) be respectively the class number and the form class number of discriminant D. Since h+(D) = h(D) if the fundamental unit has norm -1 and 2*h(D) otherwise, this sequence consists of D such that either h(D) = 1 and that the fundamental unit has norm 1, or h(D) = 2 and that the fundamental unit has norm -1.
%H A391424 Jianing Song, <a href="/A391424/b391424.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A391424 Rick L. Shepherd, <a href="https://www.digitalgreensboro.org/record/14435">Binary quadratic forms and genus theory</a>, Master of Arts Thesis, University of North Carolina at Greensboro, 2013.
%o A391424 (PARI) QFBclassno(D) = qfbclassno(D) * if (D > 0 && quadunitnorm(D) > 0, 2, 1)
%o A391424 isA391424(n) = n%4 <= 1 && !issquare(n) && QFBclassno(n) == 2 \\ quadunitnorm() requires PARI-GP of version 2.15 or higher
%Y A391424 Cf. A306638 (norms of fundamental units of orders of real quadratic fields).
%Y A391424 For a list of sequences related to the class numbers of real quadratic fields, see A087048.
%K A391424 nonn,changed
%O A391424 1,1
%A A391424 _Jianing Song_, Dec 09 2025
